     "text": [
      "PMAY (Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana) is a government-backed housing scheme in India that aims to provide affordable housing options to low-income households. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to apply for PMAY:\n",
      "\n",
      "**Eligibility:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. Age: Applicant must be at least 18 years old.\n",
      "2. Income: The household income should not exceed ₹3 lakhs per annum (approximately).\n",
      "3. Caste: The scheme is open to all sections of society, including SC/ST/OBC/EBC.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Documents required:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. Identity proof (Aadhaar card, voter ID, PAN card, or driving license)\n",
      "2. Proof of address (utility bills, rental agreement, or property deed)\n",
      "3. Income certificate (from employer or income tax returns)\n",
      "4. Caste certificate (if applicable)\n",
      "5. Marriage certificate (if applying as a married couple)\n",
      "\n",
      "**Application process:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Online application**: Visit the PMAY website ([www.pmay.gov.in](http://www.pmay.gov.in)) and click on \"Apply Now.\" Fill out the online application form with required details.\n",
      "2. **Offline application**: You can also download the application form from the PMAY website, fill it out, and submit it to your local Urban or Rural Development Authority (UDA/RDA) office.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Submission of application:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. Take a printout of the completed online application form (if applying online).\n",
      "2. Attach all required documents.\n",
      "3. Submit the application at your nearest UDA/RDA office, along with a demand draft of ₹500 (application fee).\n",
      "\n",
      "**Selection process:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. The PMAY selection committee will review and verify the applications based on eligibility criteria.\n",
      "2. Shortlisted applicants will be notified to submit additional documents or attend an interview.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Benefits:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. Interest subsidy of 6.5% per annum for a maximum period of 20 years (up to ₹2.67 lakhs).\n",
      "2. Assistance with construction costs, including the cost of building materials and labor.\n",
      "3. Priority to SC/ST/OBC/EBC applicants and those living in urban slums.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Additional tips:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. Check your eligibility before applying.\n",
      "2. Ensure you have all required documents ready before submitting the application.\n",
      "3. Be prepared for a verification process, which may involve an interview or additional document submission.\n",
      "\n",
      "Remember to apply through authorized channels only (PMAY website or local UDA/RDA office) to ensure the legitimacy of your application.\n"
     ]
    }
