     "text": [
      "PMAYU (Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana Urban) is a government scheme aimed at providing affordable housing solutions to urban poor and low-income households. To apply for PMAYU subsidy, follow these steps:\n",
      "\n",
      "**Eligibility:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. The applicant must be a citizen of India.\n",
      "2. The household income should not exceed ₹3 lakhs per annum (gross).\n",
      "3. The family should not own a pucca house in their name.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Application Process:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Identify your eligibility:** Check if you are eligible for PMAYU by visiting the official website [www.mhupa.in](http://www.mhupa.in) or contacting your local urban development department.\n",
      "2. **Gather required documents:** Collect the following documents:\n",
      "\t* Proof of identity (Aadhaar card, voter ID, etc.)\n",
      "\t* Proof of address (electricity bill, ration card, etc.)\n",
      "\t* Income certificate (latest income tax return, salary slip, etc.)\n",
      "\t* Ration card or other proof of family members\n",
      "3. **Fill the application form:** Download and fill the PMAYU application form (available on the official website) with the required information.\n",
      "4. **Submit your application:**\n",
      "\t* You can submit your application online through the PMAYU portal ([www.mhupa.in](http://www.mhupa.in)) or visit your local urban development department in person.\n",
      "5. **Verification and selection:** The application will be verified by the authorities, and a list of selected beneficiaries will be published on the official website.\n",
      "\n",
      "**PMAYU Subsidy Details:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Subsidy amount:** The maximum subsidy amount is ₹2.50 lakhs (₹3 lakhs for LIG categories).\n",
      "2. **Interest rate subvention:** You may also be eligible for an interest rate subvention of 6.5% per annum on the loan taken from a bank or financial institution.\n",
      "3. **Loan repayment period:** The loan repayment period is typically 20 years.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Additional Tips:**\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Apply early:** Apply as soon as possible, as PMAYU subsidies are limited and may be allocated on a first-come, first-served basis.\n",
      "2. **Consult authorities:** If you're unsure about the application process or have questions, consult with your local urban development department or a PMAYU officer.\n",
      "\n",
      "Remember to carefully review the PMAYU guidelines and rules before applying for the subsidy.\n"
     ]
